06/10/2002
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia -- Italian Gen Fabio Mini took command of KFOR on Friday (4 October), replacing French Gen Marcel Valentin. He is the second Italian to hold this post and the seventh commander of the peacekeepers overall. He pledged to work for peace, rule of law, and mutual respect between the various ethnic groups in the province.
In other news, Greek Defence Minister Yannos Papantoniou is calling for the EU to assume a greater role in peacekeeping in the Balkans. He was chairman of a meeting in Crete, which focused on the delay in developing Europe's defence capabilities and the problems surrounding the creation of a EU rapid reaction force. (AP, AFP, Reuters - 05/10/02; AP, AFP - 04/10/02)
